Class RakNetSession

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.whirvis.jraknet.session.RakNetSession
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GeminusRakNetPeer, UnumRakNetPeer
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    RakNetClientSession, RakNetServerSession

    public abstract class RakNetSession
extends java.lang.Object
implements UnumRakNetPeer, GeminusRakNetPeer
    This class is used to easily manage connections in RakNet.

    Trent "Whirvis" Summerlin

      • enableLatencyDetection

        public void enableLatencyDetection(boolean enabled)
        Enables/disables latency detection, when disabled the latency will always return -1. If the session is not yet in the keep alive state then the packets needed to detect the latency will not be sent until then.
        Parameters:
        enabled - whether or not latency detection is enabled
